items.name: Ext.form.field.Field
items.text:
This mixin provides a common interface for the logical behavior and state of form fields, including:

- Getter and setter methods for field values
- Events and methods for tracking value and validity changes
- Methods for triggering validation

**NOTE**: When implementing custom fields, it is most likely that you will want to extend the {@link Ext.form.field.Base}
component class rather than using this mixin directly, as BaseField contains additional logic for generating an
actual DOM complete with {@link Ext.form.Labelable} display and a form input field,
plus methods that bind the Field value getters and setters to the input field's value.

If you do want to implement this mixin directly and don't want to extend {@link Ext.form.field.Base}, then
you will most likely want to override the following methods with custom implementations: {@link #method!getValue #getValue},
{@link #method!setValue #setValue}, and {@link #method!getErrors #getErrors}. Other methods may be overridden as needed but their base
implementations should be sufficient for common cases. You will also need to make sure that {@link #method!initField #initField}
is called during the component's initialization.

items.name: disabled
items.text: True to disable the field. Disabled Fields will not be {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!submit Ext.form.Basic#submit}.

items.name: name
items.text:
The name of the field. By default this is used as the parameter name when including the
{@link #method!getSubmitData #getSubmitData} in a {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!submit Ext.form.Basic#submit}. To prevent the field from
being included in the form submit, set {@link #cfg!submitValue #submitValue} to false.

items.name: submitValue
items.text:
Setting this to false will prevent the field from being {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!submit Ext.form.Basic#submit} even when it is
not disabled.

items.name: validateOnChange
items.text:
Specifies whether this field should be validated immediately whenever a change in its value is detected.
If the validation results in a change in the field's validity, a {@link #event!validitychange #validitychange} event will be
fired. This allows the field to show feedback about the validity of its contents immediately as the user is
typing.

When set to false, feedback will not be immediate. However the form will still be validated before submitting if
the clientValidation option to {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!doAction Ext.form.Basic#doAction} is enabled, or if the field or form are validated
manually.

See also {@link Ext.form.field.Base#cfg!checkChangeEvents Ext.form.field.Base#checkChangeEvents} for controlling how changes to the field's value are
detected.

items.name: validation
items.text:
This property, when a `{@link String}`, contributes its value to the error state of this
instance as reported by `{@link #method!getErrors getErrors}`.

items.name: validationField
items.text:
When binding is used with a model, this maps to the underlying {@link Ext.data.field.Field} if
it is available. This can be used to validate the value against the model field without needing
to push the value back into the model.

items.name: value
items.text: A value to initialize this field with.

items.name: valuePublishEvent
items.text:
The event name(s) to use to publish the {@link #cfg!value #value}
{@link Ext.form.field.Base#cfg!bind Ext.form.field.Base#bind} for this field.

items.name: change
items.text:
Fires when the value of a field is changed. The value of a field is
checked for changes when the field's {@link #method!setValue #setValue} method
is called and when any of the events listed in
{@link Ext.form.field.Base#cfg!checkChangeEvents Ext.form.field.Base#checkChangeEvents} are fired.

items.name: newValue
items.text: The new value

items.name: oldValue
items.text: The original value

items.name: dirtychange
items.text: Fires when a change in the field's {@link #method!isDirty #isDirty} state is detected.

items.name: isDirty
items.text: Whether or not the field is now dirty

items.name: validitychange
items.text: Fires when a change in the field's validity is detected.

items.name: isValid
items.text: Whether or not the field is now valid

items.name: addDeprecations
items.text:
This method applies a versioned, deprecation declaration to this class. This
is typically called by the `deprecated` config.

items.name: batchChanges
items.text:
A utility for grouping a set of modifications which may trigger value changes into a single transaction, to
prevent excessive firing of {@link #event!change #change} events. This is useful for instance if the field has sub-fields which
are being updated as a group; you don't want the container field to check its own changed state for each subfield
change.

items.name: fn
items.text: The function to call with change checks suspended.

items.name: callParent
args
items.text:
The arguments, either an array or the `arguments` object
from the current method, for example: `this.callParent(arguments)`
Returns the result of calling the parent method

items.name: callSuper
args
items.text:
The arguments, either an array or the `arguments` object
from the current method, for example: `this.callSuper(arguments)`
Returns the result of calling the superclass method

items.name: checkChange
items.text:
Checks whether the value of the field has changed since the last time it was checked.
If the value has changed, it:

1. Fires the {@link #event!change #change},
2. Performs validation if the {@link #cfg!validateOnChange #validateOnChange} config is enabled, firing the
   {@link #event!validitychange #validitychange} if the validity has changed, and
3. Checks the {@link #method!isDirty #isDirty} of the field and fires the {@link #event!dirtychange #dirtychange}
   if it has changed.

items.name: checkDirty
items.text:
Checks the {@link #method!isDirty #isDirty} state of the field and if it has changed since the last time it was checked,
fires the {@link #event!dirtychange #dirtychange} event.

items.name: cleanupField
items.text:
Cleans up values initialized by this Field mixin on the current instance.
Components using this mixin should call this method before being destroyed.

items.name: clearInvalid
items.text:
Clear any invalid styles/messages for this field. Components using this mixin should implement this method to
update the components rendering to clear any existing messages.

**Note**: this method does not cause the Field's {@link #method!validate #validate} or {@link #method!isValid #isValid} methods to return `true`
if the value does not _pass_ validation. So simply clearing a field's errors will not necessarily allow
submission of forms submitted with the {@link Ext.form.action.Submit#cfg!clientValidation Ext.form.action.Submit#clientValidation} option set.

items.name: constructor
items.text: Creates new Object.

items.name: value
items.text: The value to wrap.

items.name: destroy
items.text:
This method is called to cleanup an object and its resources. After calling
this method, the object should not be used any further.

items.name: didValueChange
items.text:
Checks if the value has changed. Allows subclasses to override for
any more complex logic.

items.name: extractFileInput
items.text:
Only relevant if the instance's {@link #method!isFileUpload #isFileUpload} method returns true. Returns a reference to the file input
DOM element holding the user's selected file. The input will be appended into the submission form and will not be
returned, so this method should also create a replacement.

items.name: getConfig
items.text:
Returns a specified config property value. If the name parameter is not passed,
all current configuration options will be returned as key value pairs.

items.name: name
items.text: The name of the config property to get.

items.name: peek
items.text: `true` to peek at the raw value without calling the getter.
The config property value.

items.name: getErrors
items.text:
Runs this field's validators and returns an array of error messages for any validation failures. This is called
internally during validation and would not usually need to be used manually.

Each subclass should override or augment the return value to provide their own errors.

items.name: value
items.text: The value to get errors for (defaults to the current field value)
All error messages for this field; an empty Array if none.

items.name: getInitialConfig
name
items.text: Name of the config option to return.

The full config object or a single config value
when `{@link #cfg!name name}` parameter specified.

items.name: getModelData
items.text:
Returns the value(s) that should be saved to the {@link Ext.data.Model} instance for this field, when {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!updateRecord Ext.form.Basic#updateRecord} is called. Typically this will be an object with a single name-value pair, the name
being this field's {@link #getName name} and the value being its current data value. More advanced field
implementations may return more than one name-value pair. The returned values will be saved to the corresponding
field names in the Model.

Note that the values returned from this method are not guaranteed to have been successfully {@link #method!validate #validate}.

A mapping of submit parameter names to values; each value should be a string, or an array of
strings if that particular name has multiple values. It can also return null if there are no parameters to be
submitted.

items.name: getName
items.text:
Returns the {@link Ext.form.field.Field#cfg!name Ext.form.field.Field#name} attribute of the field. This is used as the parameter name
when including the field value in a {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!submit Ext.form.Basic#submit}.
name The field {@link Ext.form.field.Field#cfg!name Ext.form.field.Field#name}

items.name: getSubmitData
items.text:
Returns the parameter(s) that would be included in a standard form submit for this field. Typically this will be
an object with a single name-value pair, the name being this field's {@link #getName name} and the value being
its current stringified value. More advanced field implementations may return more than one name-value pair.

Note that the values returned from this method are not guaranteed to have been successfully {@link #method!validate #validate}.

A mapping of submit parameter names to values; each value should be a string, or an array of
strings if that particular name has multiple values. It can also return null if there are no parameters to be
submitted.

items.name: getValue
items.text:
Returns the current data value of the field. The type of value returned is particular to the type of the
particular field (e.g. a Date object for {@link Ext.form.field.Date}).
value The field value

items.name: hasOwnProperty
prop
items.text: The name of the property to test.

Returns true if object contains specified property; else
returns false.

items.name: initConfig

items.text: this

items.name: initField
items.text:
Initializes this Field mixin on the current instance. Components using this mixin should call this method during
their own initialization process.

items.name: initValue
items.text: Initializes the field's value based on the initial config.

items.name: isDirty
items.text:
Returns true if the value of this Field has been changed from its {@link #property!originalValue #originalValue}.
Will always return false if the field is disabled.

Note that if the owning {@link Ext.form.Basic} was configured with
{@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!trackResetOnLoad Ext.form.Basic#trackResetOnLoad} then the {@link #property!originalValue #originalValue} is updated when
the values are loaded by {@link Ext.form.Basic}.{@link Ext.form.Basic#method!setValues Ext.form.Basic#setValues}.

True if this field has been changed from its original value (and is not disabled),
false otherwise.

items.name: isEqual
items.text:
Returns whether two field {@link #method!getValue #getValue} are logically equal. Field implementations may override this
to provide custom comparison logic appropriate for the particular field's data type.

items.name: value1
items.text: The first value to compare

items.name: value2
items.text: The second value to compare
True if the values are equal, false if inequal.

items.name: isEqualAsString
items.text:
Returns whether two values are logically equal.
Similar to {@link #method!isEqual #isEqual}, however null or undefined values will be treated as empty strings.

items.name: value1
items.text: The first value to compare

items.name: value2
items.text: The second value to compare
True if the values are equal, false if inequal.

items.name: isFileUpload
items.text:
Returns whether this Field is a file upload field; if it returns true, forms will use special techniques for
{@link Ext.form.Basic#method!submit Ext.form.Basic#submit} via AJAX. See {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!hasUpload Ext.form.Basic#hasUpload} for details. If
this returns true, the {@link #method!extractFileInput #extractFileInput} method must also be implemented to return the corresponding file
input element.

items.name: isPrototypeOf
prototype
items.text:
an object to be tested against each link in the prototype chain of the
*object* argument

items.name: object
items.text: the object whose prototype chain will be searched
Returns true if object is a prototype and false if not.

items.name: isValid
items.text:
Returns whether or not the field value is currently valid by {@link #method!getErrors #getErrors} the field's current
value. The {@link #event!validitychange #validitychange} event will not be fired; use {@link #method!validate #validate} instead if you want the event
to fire. **Note**: {@link #cfg!disabled #disabled} fields are always treated as valid.

Implementations are encouraged to ensure that this method does not have side-effects such as triggering error
message display.
True if the value is valid, else false

items.name: link
items.text:
Adds a "destroyable" object to an internal list of objects that will be destroyed
when this instance is destroyed (via `{@link #method!destroy #destroy}`).
The `{@link #cfg!value value}` passed.

items.name: markInvalid
errors
items.text: The validation message(s) to display.

items.name: onChange
items.text:
Called when the field's value changes. Performs validation if the {@link #cfg!validateOnChange #validateOnChange}
config is enabled, and invokes the dirty check.

items.name: onDirtyChange
items.text: Called when the field's dirty state changes.

items.name: propertyIsEnumerable
prop
items.text: The name of the property to test.

If the object does not have the specified property, this
method returns false.

items.name: publishValue
items.text: Publish the value of this field.

items.name: reset
items.text: Resets the current field value to the originally loaded value and clears any validation messages. See {@link Ext.form.Basic}.{@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!trackResetOnLoad Ext.form.Basic#trackResetOnLoad}

items.name: resetOriginalValue
items.text:
Resets the field's {@link #property!originalValue #originalValue} property so it matches the current {@link #method!getValue #getValue}. This is
called by {@link Ext.form.Basic}.{@link Ext.form.Basic#method!setValues Ext.form.Basic#setValues} if the form's
{@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!trackResetOnLoad Ext.form.Basic#trackResetOnLoad} property is set to true.

items.name: setConfig
items.text: Sets a single/multiple configuration options.

items.name: name
items.text: The name of the property to set, or a set of key value pairs to set.

items.name: value
items.text: The value to set for the name parameter.
this

items.name: setValue
items.text: Sets a data value into the field and runs the change detection and validation.

items.name: value
items.text: The value to set
this

items.name: statics
toLocaleString
items.text:
Returns a string representing the object. This method is meant to be overridden by derived objects
for locale-specific purposes.

`{@link Object}`'s `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}` returns the result of calling `{@link #method!toString toString}`.

This function is provided to give objects a generic `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}` method, even though not all
may use it. Currently, only `{@link Array}`, `{@link Number}`, and `{@link Date}` override `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}`.
Object represented as a string.

items.name: toString

items.text: Object represented as a string.

items.name: unlink
items.text:
Destroys a given set of `{@link #method!link #link}` objects. This is only needed if
the linked object is being destroyed before this instance.

items.name: names
items.text: The names of the linked objects to destroy.
this

items.name: validate
items.text:
Returns whether or not the field value is currently valid by {@link #method!getErrors #getErrors} the field's current
value, and fires the {@link #event!validitychange #validitychange} event if the field's validity has changed since the last validation.
**Note**: {@link #cfg!disabled #disabled} fields are always treated as valid.

Custom implementations of this method are allowed to have side-effects such as triggering error message display.
To validate without side-effects, use {@link #method!isValid #isValid}.
True if the value is valid, else false

items.name: valueOf
items.text:
Returns the primitive value of the specified object.

JavaScript calls the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method to convert an object to a primitive value. You rarely need to
invoke the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method yourself; JavaScript automatically invokes it when encountering an
object where a primitive value is expected.

By default, the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method is inherited by every object descended from `{@link Object}`. Every built-
in core object overrides this method to return an appropriate value. If an object has no primitive
value, `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` returns the object itself, which is displayed as:

    [object Object]

You can use `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` within your own code to convert a built-in object into a primitive value.
When you create a custom object, you can override `Object.valueOf` to call a custom method instead
of the default `{@link Object}` method.

You can create a function to be called in place of the default `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method. Your function must
take no arguments.

Suppose you have an object type `myNumberType` and you want to create a `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method for it.
The following code assigns a user-defined function to the object's valueOf method:

    myNumberType.prototype.valueOf = new Function(functionText)

With the preceding code in place, any time an object of type `myNumberType` is used in a context
where it is to be represented as a primitive value, JavaScript automatically calls the function
defined in the preceding code.

An object's `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method is usually invoked by JavaScript, but you can invoke it yourself as
follows:

    myNumber.valueOf()

Note: Objects in string contexts convert via the `{@link #method!toString toString}` method, which is different from
`{@link String}` objects converting to string primitives using `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}`. All objects have a string
conversion, if only `"[object type]"`. But many objects do not convert to number, boolean, or
function.
Returns value of the object or the object itself.

items.name: $configPrefixed
items.text:
The value `true` causes `config` values to be stored on instances using a
property name prefixed with an underscore ("_") character. A value of `false`
stores `config` values as properties using their exact name (no prefix).

items.name: $configStrict
items.text:
The value `true` instructs the `{@link #method!initConfig initConfig}` method to only honor values for
properties declared in the `config` block of a class. When `false`, properties
that are not declared in a `config` block will be placed on the instance.

items.text: Template method before a field is reset.

destroyed

items.name: dirty

items.name: isConfiguring
items.text: This property is set to `true` during the call to `{@link #method!initConfig initConfig}`.

items.name: isFirstInstance
items.text: This property is set to `true` if this instance is the first of its class.

items.name: isFormField
items.text: Flag denoting that this component is a Field. Always true.

items.name: isInstance
items.text:
This value is `true` and is used to identify plain objects from instances of
a defined class.

items.name: originalValue
items.text:
The original value of the field as configured in the {@link #cfg!value #value} configuration, or as loaded by the last
form load operation if the form's {@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!trackResetOnLoad Ext.form.Basic#trackResetOnLoad} setting is `true`.
